We note that $9y^2-30y+25$ looks almost like $(3y)^2 - 2(3y)(5) + 5^2 = (3y - 5)^2$, except that the constant term is $25$ instead of $5^2$. We can fix this by adding and subtracting $2(3y)(5) = 30y$: \begin{align*}
9y^2-30y+25 &= 9y^2 - 30y + 30y - 30y + 25 \\
&= 9y^2 - 2(3y)(5) + 5^2 - 30y \\
&= (3y - 5)^2 - 30y \\
&= \boxed{(3y-5)^2-30y}.
\end{align*}
